B32-pO.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/0*72oraIPnETB32-pO.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/0*72oraIPnETB32-pO.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/0*72oraIPnETB32-pO.png 1400w"/><img alt="" loading="lazy" role="presentation" src="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:700/0*72oraIPnETB32-pO.png"></picture></div><p class="mbr-description mbr-fonts-style mt-2 align-center display-12 text-muted" style="font-size:12px;">Image credits: -<a href="https://www.activestate.com/blog/neural-network-showdown-tensorflow-vs-pytorch/" target="_self">ActiveState</a></p><br></div></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">To answer this question, we’ll have to take different sectors where varied applications are valid and taken into consideration.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><h4 class="mbr-section-subtitle mbr-fonts-style mb-4 display-5">The industry</h4></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">you’re in an industry setup based on deep learning, you’re likely using TensorFlow and should probably stick with it. TensorFlow’s robust deployment framework and extended platform are invaluable for those who need models that can soon go into production. Easy deployment on a gRPC (Google Remote Procedure Call) server along with model monitoring and artefact tracking <em>(a byproduct of software development that helps in describing the architecture, design, and function of the software)</em> are critical tools for industry use.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">With the recent release of Torch Serve, you might be considering using PyTorch (only if you have a solid backed up reason) to access SOTA (State of the Art) models available in PyTorch.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;"><mark>If you’re building mobile applications, you can consider using PyTorch given the recent release of PyTorch Live, but at some point, you’ll be needing audio or video input and at that point, TensorFlow comes into the game.</mark></p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><h4 class="mbr-section-subtitle mbr-fonts-style mb-4 display-5">Research</h4></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">If you’re a researcher or into research, you should be using PyTorch because working in that pythonic environment helps in avoiding complexity.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">There are a few exemptions to this rule, the most notable being that those in Reinforcement Learning should consider using TensorFlow. For Reinforcement Learning TensorFlow has a Native Agent Library accompanied by DeepMind’s Acme framework providing a perfect environment to cater needs.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
