pm3gDR.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/0*pZD2vQqON3pm3gDR.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/0*pZD2vQqON3pm3gDR.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/0*pZD2vQqON3pm3gDR.png 1400w"/><img alt="" loading="lazy" role="presentation" src="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:700/0*pZD2vQqON3pm3gDR.png"></picture></div><p class="mbr-description mbr-fonts-style mt-2 align-center display-12 text-muted" style="font-size:12px;">Image Credits: -<a href="https://www.imaginarycloud.com/blog/pytorch-vs-tensorflow/" target="_self">Imaginary Cloud</a></p><br></div></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">In TensorFlow we can also see the implementation of OpenAI’s Baseline model repository but is not specific to any one platform because it can be used in both TensorFlow and PyTorch.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">If you do not want to use TensorFlow, you should consider exploring Google’s JAX if you are doing <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tensor_Processing_Unit" target="_self">TPU (Tensor Processing Unit)</a> training. It is not a neural network framework itself, but closer to implementation of NumPy and would give you a pythonic experience. For alternatives, you can look for Google’s Flax.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">If TPU trainings are not a part of your schedule, then the best move to make would be sticking with PyTorch.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Whichever framework you choose, you should keep your eye on JAX (The conference for Java and Software Innovation) in 2022, especially as its community grows and more publications begin utilising it.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><h4 class="mbr-section-subtitle mbr-fonts-style mb-4 display-5">Professor/Student</h4></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">If you’re a professor/student, which framework to use for deep Learning completely depends on the goals and the results you want to achieve.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">For students, if your focus is to be an industry-ready Deep Learning engineer who can zap the entire Deep Learning process, not just Deep Learning theory, then you should use TensorFlow. In this case, exposure to the TensorFlow ecosystem and its tools along with practice projects will be very instructive and valuable.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-12 col-lg-9">
